I drained the tofu and rolled them in a mixture of nutritional yeast, corn starch, garlic/onion powder seasoning, and panko crumbs. Popped in the air fryer to crisp them up and they were delicious with some volcano sauce!  Roasted the broccoli in hoisin sauce and, while it was delicious, either the oven wasn't hot enough or it's not a good roasting sauce because it carmelized mostly and the broccoli was....chewy. 

And another cup of green tea from Simply Balanced. üçµ I'm trying to work myself up to 3/day with each meal to see if it has an effect on my energy and overall loss. Only time will tell!‚ú®

(317 cal) 20NC, 17F, 17P

Extra Firm Tofu, 3.2 oz

Breading consisted of nutritional yeast flakes, panko bread crumbs, corn starch, and seasonings

Roasted Broccoli in Hoisin Sauce, 93 g / 1 tbsp

